====================================================================
  PRINTERPC – WIRELESS GOOGLE PHOTOS PRINTER FOR EPSON L4260 (macOS)
====================================================================

This turns any Mac into a wireless print server:
→ Send a Google Photos link from your phone → it prints instantly on the L4260.
No drivers, no cables, no apps. Just Wi-Fi + AirPrint.

────────────────────────────────────
1. ONE-TIME PRINTER SETUP (3–5 minutes)
────────────────────────────────────
Do this directly on the Epson L4260 touchscreen:

1. Press Home → Wi-Fi Setup → Wi-Fi Setup Wizard
2. Choose your home Wi-Fi network
3. Enter your Wi-Fi password using the touchscreen
4. Wait until you see the blue Wi-Fi icon and “Connected”

That’s it. The printer now has AirPrint enabled.

────────────────────────────────────
2. ONE-TIME MAC CHECK (30 seconds)
────────────────────────────────────
1. Make sure your Mac is on the SAME Wi-Fi as the printer
2. Open System Settings → Printers & Scanners
   → “EPSON L4260 Series” should appear automatically

3. Open Terminal and run:
   lpstat -p | grep -i l4260

   You should see something like:
   printer EPSON_L4260_Series is idle...

If you see that line → everything is ready.

────────────────────────────────────
3. RUN THE NODE.JS SCRIPT
────────────────────────────────────
Requirements (one-time):
   npm install socket.io-client axios

Then just run:
   node printer/index.js

First run will ask for your WebSocket server URL (example):
   http://192.168.1.100:3000

(Change 192.168.1.100 to the actual IP of the machine running the chat/server)

The script will show:
   Connected & registered as "PrinterPC"
   Ready for :print- links!

────────────────────────────────────
4. HOW TO PRINT FROM YOUR PHONE
────────────────────────────────────
In your chat app (or wherever the WebSocket server is connected), just type:

   :print-https://your-google-photos-link-here

Example:
   :print-https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/ABCD1234...

The Mac will:
   → Download the photo in high quality
   → Auto-scale to A4
   → Print wirelessly via AirPrint
   → Delete the temp file

Done in 10–20 seconds.

────────────────────────────────────
TROUBLESHOOTING
────────────────────────────────────
• Printer not found? → Double-check both devices are on the SAME Wi-Fi
• Still nothing? → Restart the printer once (helps Bonjour discovery)
• Test manually:
    echo "test" | lp -d "EPSON_L4260_Series"
  If that prints → the script will work too

